the community.

00:11:13.630 --> 00:11:17.510
Not people necessarily related to
the Army were attending the school.

00:11:17.510 --> 00:11:19.840
One student-- I was
in the seventh grade--

00:11:19.840 --> 00:11:23.790
one student approached me and she
asked me something in Spanish.

00:11:23.790 --> 00:11:25.880
And, I just blankly stared at her.

00:11:25.880 --> 00:11:27.980
I had no idea what she was asking.

00:11:27.980 --> 00:11:29.280
So, she thought I hadn't heard her,

00:11:29.280 --> 00:11:32.180
so she repeats the
question in Spanish.

00:11:32.180 --> 00:11:34.460
And, I was just, again,
and she says--

00:11:34.460 --> 00:11:37.880
and then she said to me in
English, don't you understand?

00:11:37.880 --> 00:11:40.190
And I said, no.

00:11:40.190 --> 00:11:42.440
And she says, what kind
of a Mexican are you?

00:11:42.440 --> 00:11:45.540
[laughter] And I said, oh my-- .

00:11:45.540 --> 00:11:47.850
I was just shocked.

00:11:47.850 --> 00:11:49.150
I didn't know-- .

00:11:49.150 --> 00:11:50.460
I didn't say anything.

00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:55.950
I was thinking, I had never thought
of myself, you know, as Mexican,

00:11:55.950 --> 00:11:58.580
as Puerto Rican, as
I was just American.

00:11:58.580 --> 00:11:59.890
I was just an Army brat.

00:11:59.890 --> 00:12:02.470
I was just in middle school.

00:12:02.470 --> 00:12:04.860
I really had no idea, but it
was like a slap in the face.

00:12:04.860 --> 00:12:07.760
And I'm thinking, my goodness,
what kind of Mexican am I?

00:12:07.760 --> 00:12:09.060
I don't know.

00:12:09.060 --> 00:12:10.360
I don't know.

00:12:10.360 --> 00:12:11.660
I don't know.

00:12:11.660 --> 00:12:12.960
I guess I'm not a Mexican.

