00:28:45.190 --> 00:28:47.380
Okay. And, conclusion.

00:28:47.380 --> 00:28:50.790
The quest for determining the
link between language and identity

00:28:50.790 --> 00:28:54.960
on the island of Puerto Rico has
lead to thought provoking results.

00:28:54.960 --> 00:28:58.290
The traditional viewpoint of
promoting Puerto Rican Spanish

00:28:58.290 --> 00:29:02.770
as the bearer of Puerto Rican
identity and American English

00:29:02.770 --> 00:29:07.490 position:56%
as the bearer of unwelcome
intrusion now appears to be evolving

00:29:07.490 --> 00:29:10.670
into a modern attitude
of acceptance of the idea

00:29:10.670 --> 00:29:14.810
that languages can function
independently of identity.

00:29:14.810 --> 00:29:19.050
Also, the two cultures present on
the island seem to be entwining

00:29:19.050 --> 00:29:23.300
and creating a syncretic new
variety unique to Puerto Rico.

00:29:23.300 --> 00:29:28.550
To all appearances, it seems that
a new identity is being forged.

00:29:28.550 --> 00:29:31.430
One that is not linked to
any particular language,

00:29:31.430 --> 00:29:33.860
but rather includes
the heart of a people

00:29:33.860 --> 00:29:38.560
and their evolving traditions,
customs, and beliefs.

